-- Clinton Urges Broader Counterterrorism Cooperation Wtih Algeria
-- B y   N i c o l e   G a o u e t t e
-- 2013-01-18T19:47:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-18/clinton-urges-broader-counterterrorism-cooperation-wtih-algeria.html
Secretary of State  Hillary Clinton 
said the U.S. should broaden its counter-terrorism cooperation
with Algeria and other North African countries.  Clinton, speaking in Washington at the State Department,
extended her condolences to families of hostages killed in
Algeria and said the U.S. is working with Algeria to address the
challenge.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicole Gaouette in Washington at 
